---
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A public demand board for local ownership, clean uninstall, app accountability, and better platform stewardship."
    />
    <title>Take Back the Mac</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="/">
        <span class="brand-mark" aria-hidden="true">TBM</span>
        <span>Take Back the Mac</span>
      </a>
      <nav aria-label="Primary">
        <a href="/manifesto/">Manifesto</a>
        <a href="#rights">What we want</a>
        <a href="#idea-form">Add a demand</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero" id="about">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="tagline">The Mac is not vendor territory.</p>
          <h1>The machine I paid for should behave like mine.</h1>
          <div class="hero-body">
            <p class="section-kicker">Manifesto</p>
            <p>
              This is a simple argument: Apple has enough control to make the
              Mac cleaner, safer, and more respectful. If it wants that control,
              it should use it to defend the user.
            </p>
            <p>
              The Mac should be a trusted personal computer, not a place where
              every app leaves a private mess and every owner becomes a
              part-time system administrator. Clean uninstall, visible app
              footprints, honest background behavior, and a better App Store
              are not power user luxuries. They are table stakes for an owned
              device.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href="/manifesto/">Read the whole manifesto</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="rights-section" id="rights" aria-labelledby="rights-heading">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <h2 id="rights-heading">What we want</h2>
          <p>
            The first demands are here. Upvote what Apple should make real
            first.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rights-list" id="rights-list"></div>

        <div class="ideas-panel submitted-demands" id="submitted-demands" hidden>
          <div class="ideas-toolbar">
            <h3>Submitted demands</h3>
            <div class="segmented" aria-label="Sort submitted demands">
              <button type="button" data-idea-sort="top" aria-pressed="true">Top</button>
              <button type="button" data-idea-sort="new" aria-pressed="false">New</button>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-list" id="idea-list" aria-live="polite"></div>
        </div>

        <form class="idea-form demand-form" id="idea-form">
          <div class="form-intro">
            <h3>Add your own demand</h3>
            <p>
              If something is missing, add it here. Specific demands beat vague
              frustration.
            </p>
          </div>
          <label>
            <span>Title</span>
            <input
              name="title"
              type="text"
              maxlength="120"
              required
              placeholder="Uninstall should show every file an app created"
            />
          </label>
          <label>
            <span>Details</span>
            <textarea
              name="body"
              maxlength="1200"
              rows="5"
              placeholder="What should Apple change? What pain does it remove?"
            ></textarea>
          </label>
          <div class="form-row">
            <label>
              <span>Email</span>
              <input
                name="email"
                type="email"
                maxlength="254"
                required
                autocomplete="email"
                placeholder="you@example.com"
              />
            </label>
            <label>
              <span>Name optional</span>
              <input name="author" type="text" maxlength="80" placeholder="Your name" />
            </label>
          </div>
          <button class="button primary" type="submit">Submit demand</button>
          <p class="status" id="idea-form-status" aria-live="polite"></p>
        </form>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <span>That's a Mac, Jack.</span>
      <a href="https://paulwelty.com">Started by Paul Welty</a>
      <a href="https://marco.org/2026/04/01/letter-to-john-ternus">Inspired in part by Marco Arment's letter to John Ternus</a>
    </footer>

    <script src="/app.js" type="module"></script>
  </body>
</html>
